:PATH
Run Your Recipe Through a Soap Calculator
Before weighing anything, enter your oil blend at Soapcalc.net or SoapMaker3.
|
:INFO
Run Your Recipe Through a Soap Calculator
Before weighing anything, enter your oil blend at Soapcalc.net or SoapMaker3. A simple \
beginner recipe: 40 percent olive oil, 30 percent coconut oil, 30 percent palm oil (or \
lard). The calculator outputs the exact lye and water amounts for your batch

:PATH
Mix the Lye Solution
Weigh distilled water into a heat-safe container (HDPE plastic or stainless).
|
:INFO
Mix the Lye Solution
Weigh distilled water into a heat-safe container (HDPE plastic or stainless). Weigh lye \
separately. Always add lye to water, never water to lye: adding water to lye creates a \
violent reaction and can spatter. Stir slowly. The solution will reach 180 to

:PATH
Combine Oils and Reach Trace
Melt hard oils (coconut, palm) and combine with liquid oils (olive, castor).
|
:INFO
Combine Oils and Reach Trace
Melt hard oils (coconut, palm) and combine with liquid oils (olive, castor). Bring to \
roughly the same temperature as your cooled lye solution (90 to 110 F). Slowly pour lye \
solution into the oils while stick-blending in short bursts. Trace is reached

